# ==============================================================================
# .gitignore for the cc-research-assistant TEMPLATE repo
#
# Philosophy: this repo tracks its full folder structure so forks start with
# a complete scaffold. Almost nothing is actively ignored here.
#
# Downstream projects should UNCOMMENT the sections below to protect data,
# build artifacts, and generated outputs.
# ==============================================================================


# ── Always ignored: OS noise and editor swap files ──
# These are never meaningful content in any repo.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ── Always ignored: Claude Code machine-local settings ──
# settings.local.json contains machine-specific paths and should never be shared.
# Real state files are runtime artifacts; *.example files ARE tracked as scaffolding.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/state/*
!.claude/state/*.example

# ── Always ignored: Quarto runtime cache ──
# Generated by the Quarto VS Code extension language server even without rendering.
.quarto/


# ==============================================================================
# ── Add in downstream projects ──
# None of the blocks below apply to the template itself. Uncomment after forking.
# ==============================================================================

# ── LaTeX build artifacts ──
# *.aux
# *.bbl
# *.blg
# *.fdb_latexmk
# *.fls
# *.log
# *.nav
# *.out
# *.snm
# *.toc
# *.vrb
# *.synctex.gz
# *.run.xml
# *-blx.bib

# ── Compiled PDFs ──
# *.pdf

# ── Python cache ──
# __pycache__/
# *.pyc
# *.pyo

# ── R session files ──
# .Rhistory
# .RData
# .Rdata
# .Rproj.user/

# ── IDE project files (optional — some teams track these) ──
# .vscode/
# .idea/

# ── Quarto / LaTeX compilation outputs ──
# /.quarto/
# paper/.quarto/
# paper/quarto/*_files/
# paper/quarto/.quarto/
# _output/

# ── Generated HTML reports ──
# project_dashboard.html
# research_overview.html
# quality_reports/**/*.html

# ── Built documentation site ──
# docs/

# ── Cleaned datasets (regenerated from scripts; often large) ──
# data/cleaned/*.rds
# data/cleaned/*.csv
# data/cleaned/*.parquet

# ── Raw data (download via replication instructions; never commit) ──
# data/raw/**/*.zip
# data/raw/**/*.npy
# data/raw/**/*.csv
# data/raw/**/*.dta
# data/raw/**/*.do
# data/raw/**/*.xlsx
# data/raw/**/*.xls
